354.720.  Annual report, required, content. — 1.  Every prepaid dental plan corporation shall file with the director annually, on or before March first, a report verified by at least two principal officers covering the preceding calendar year.
  2.  Such report shall be on forms prescribed by the director and shall include:
  (1)  A financial statement of the corporation, including its balance sheet and receipts and disbursements for the preceding year;
  (2)  Any material changes in the information submitted pursuant to section 354.704;
  (3)  The number of persons enrolled during the year, the number of enrollees as of the end of the year, and the number of enrollments terminated during the year.
(L. 1987 S.B. 272 § 10)
